10. Pension Planning RPG

Target stakeholders: Members, nearing-retirement employees, young workers
Game format: Role-playing financial planning game

The player controls a worker’s career and retirement decisions. The game shows how long-term contributions affect pension, PF accumulation, and retirement security.

Learning outcomes:

Members understand why early withdrawal can reduce long-term benefits.

Example choices:

Withdraw PF after job loss
Transfer PF to new employer
Continue service for pension eligibility
Update nominee
Plan retirement age
Choose between short-term consumption and long-term security

Gamification:

Retirement security meter, family protection score, pension continuity score.
